features: These 4 Packs of compact Oxford Poly Spiral Notebooks have neutral colored covers, 80 sheets of thick 120 gsm white paper with gray college ruled lines, and a silver twin-wire spiral binding
Small 5.7 inch x 8.5 inch notebooks are the perfect size for all of your on-the-go activities; great for writing and note taking wherever you are; 1 each in khaki, peach, light blue, light green
Thick, semi-translucent covers in our calming color pallet give these books a muted, modern aesthetic and wear & tear durability; a privacy sheet inside keeps your notes confidential
This premium paper is a thicker, smooth 120 gsm paper, so ink doesn't bleed through the pages when you're writing or journaling; perfect for work, school and home
Notebooks have a silver no-snag coil that provides a sturdy binding that won't catch on items; notebooks lay flat or flip all the way around while you're writing and taking notes
body.description: These Oxford Poly Spiral Notebooks are small in size, but big on aesthetics. Each 5.7 x 8.5 inch spiral notebook has neutral semi-translucent covers that are wear and tear-resistant for durability. A thoughtful unperforated privacy sheet inside keeps your writing confidential. Snag-resistant silver twin-loop binding holds 80 college ruled sheets of perforated notebook paper and allows your note book to lay completely flat while you work. When you're ready to start writing, you will love this paper! Thick, heavyweight 32 lb/120 gsm paper is smooth and won't show excessive bleed-through on the pages. These college ruled notebooks are lined with a distinctive gray rule that doesn't compete with your handwriting. Pages are perforated and detatch to 5.1" x 8.5". The 8.5 x 5.7 size book is compact enough to carry for the office, school, journal work or for meeting notes throughout the day. 4 pack in our calm color palette in khaki, peach, light blue, light green.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars durable, water resistant cover, high quality notebooks
reviews.reviewText: I was pleasantly surprised when I received my set of four Oxford Poly Spiral Notebooks, I guess I didn't read the description closely enough, but am delighted with the quality of the notebooks. I tend to carry a notebook with me for jotting notes from work or home projects. These notebooks are attractive; sturdy (front and back covers are made of strong and water resistant vinal); the loops on the spiral bindings are large and strong (no fear of bindings coming undone) allowing you to open the notebook flat (two pages showing), or flip the pages completely around to minimize size; the pages are firm but not too heavy with plenty of lines to write on; and the notebook easily fits inside a purse or computer bag. Great value as well!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: The paper is thick and heavy ink does not bleed through. The papers turn smoothly, and the pages are lined. I like the no snag spiral as well. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This review is for the Oxford Poly Spiral Notebooks, Small 5.7 x 8.5 Book, Thick Poly Cover, White Paper, College Rule, 80 Sheets/160 Pages, Neutral Colors, 4 Pack (69721).I got these to use as a daily planner- I much prefer something like a line or grid notebook to organize my lists and tasks. These notebooks are of a good quality. The cover is light and thick and is slightly wider than the paper to protect the pages. The pages turn easily on the wire binding and the ends of the wire are inside the back cover to minimize snagging or scratching. The first page is a glossy paper sheet. The college lined pages are thick and the perforations are smooth. The Neutral Colors covers are a little more dull and washed out than neutral in my opinion but I consider that to be a personal preference rather than a negative. Overall I found these notebooks to be as described and of a very good quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Portable notebooks in cute colors!
reviews.reviewText: I go through notebooks really quickly and frequently need to take them with me in my purse, in travel bags etc. so these smaller sized ones are perfect! This is a really great value pack of good quality notebooks. The covers are nice and sturdy and they feel well made. No issues with them getting bend or torn up in transport so far. The pages are nice and take ink well, and I think these have the perfect number of pages--not too thick but plenty of room to write in. I am very happy with these and the colors are just so pretty!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Well-made, durable, useful
reviews.reviewText: The non-snagging design of the coiled spiral binding is a brilliant feature. Who has not snagged a favorite sweater on the old-style spiral binding while carrying an armload of notebooks in a classroom? A very thoughtful design improvement.The pages are of thick paper, and neither ballpoint nor felt-tipped pen ink bleeds through to the back of the page. These open flat, so I find them useful for field notes. The coves are heavy and durable and stand up to a little mist, and in the shoulder seasons are certainly more economical than waterproof notebooks. The different colored covers allow for color-coding. The muted colors - cantaloupe and honeydew melon - are not my favorites, but perhaps offer more camouflage to birders in the field or those on cryptic missions.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Even though I'm left-handed, I like these spiral notebooks, especially because of the perforated pages. The colors are a bit TOO neutral for my tastes (the covers are a lot more transparent in-person than the product page photos show), but the size is great for my needs.
